sonby United|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |23 (7t,1c)\n|-\n| \u00a0style=\"text-align:center;\" |\u00a0 4 ||Joe Bennett||Newton Rangers|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |23 (3t,4c,3p)\n|-\n| \u00a0style=\"text-align:center;\" |\u00a0 6 ||[[Frederick Gladding]]||North Shore Albions|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |17 (3t,3c,1p)\n|-\n| \u00a0style=\"text-align:center;\" |\u00a0 7 ||Harris||Eden Ramblers|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |15 (5t)\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Lower Grades==\nGrades were made of the following teams with the winning team in bold:\n*'''First Juniors''': [[City Rovers]], [[North Shore Albions]], [[Northcote Tigers|Northcote & Birkenhead Rambers]], [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]]\n*'''Third Juniors''': [[City Rovers]], [[Eden Ramblers]], [[North Shore Albions]], [[Northcote Tigers|Northcote & Birkenhead Ramblers]], [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]]\n\n==Representative Season==\nThe season began with a match against the New Zealand team which was about to depart for its Australian tour. The touring side won by two points but when they returned from their tour they played again only this time Auckland were the victors by 11 points to 3.\n\n===Auckland v New Zealand===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 10 June\n| time =\n| home = Auckland\n| score =14\u201316\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =New Zealand v Auckland/Win for Dominion Team\n| page = 8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLII| issue=138\n| date = 1911-06-12\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19110612.2.82\n| accessdate = 2019-12-15}}</ref>\n| away = New Zealand\n| try1 = George Harrison, [[Harry Fricker]], Joe Bennett 2\n| con1 = S Cole\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[George A. Gillett|George Gillett]], [[Roy Siddells]], [[Ernie Buckland]], [[Dave Mason (rugby league)|Dave Mason]]\n| con2 = [[Arthur Francis (rugby)|Arthur Francis]] 2\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Takapuna Racecourse\n| attendance =\n| referee = R Oliphant\n}}\n\n===Auckland v New Zealand===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 29 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 11\u20133\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =New Zealand v Auckland\n| page = 8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLII| issue=180\n| date = 1911-07-31\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19110731.2.97\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref>\n| away = New Zealand\n| try1 = J Kay, [[Arthur Carlaw]], [[Stan Walters (rugby league)|Stan Walters]]\n| con1 = [[Albert Asher]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Ernie Buckland]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Takapuna Racecourse\n| attendance =\n| referee = Bob Oliphant\n}}\n\n===Auckland v Wellington (Northern Union Cup)===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 5 Aug\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 16\u20138\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =First Challenge Match/Wellington v Auckland\n| page = 8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLII| issue=186\n| date = 1911-08-07\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19110807.2.75\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref>\n| away = Wellington\n| try1 = J Kay 2, [[Albert Asher]], Jim Bennett\n| con1 = [[Frank Morse (rugby league)|Frank Morse]]\n| pen1 = [[Frank Morse (rugby league)|Frank Morse]]\n| try2 = [[Bob Mitchell (rugby league)|Bob Mitchell]] 2\n| con2 = A Seeling\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 5000\n| referee = Cunningham\n}}\n\n===Auckland v Lower Waikato===\nJ Kay had the distinction of playing for Auckland one week, and then turning out against them the following week for Waikato. Occasionally players from the Waikato and Bay of Plenty regions would represent Auckland. Kay played 3 matches for Auckland in this season. The Auckland Star credited a conversion to Jim Griffen while the New Zealand Herald reported that [[Charles Dunning]] kicked all 3 goals. As the Auckland Star's match report was more detailed that is the record reported below.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 12 August\n| time =\n| home = Lower Waikato\n| score = 22\u201336\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\