Jim Griffen]] 2, [[Harry Fricker]], George Harrison, [[Stan Walters (rugby league)|Stan Walters]]\n| con1 = [[Charles Dunning]] 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Cederman 2\n| con2 = Cederman 2\n| pen2 = [[Dave Mason (rugby league)|Dave Mason]]\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 5000\n| referee = McCarthy\n}}\n\n===Auckland v Taranaki (Northern Union Cup)===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 September\n| time =\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 26\u201315\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Interprovincial Cup/Auckland Beats Taranaki/A Record Attendance\n| page = 9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=XLVIII| issue=147686\n| date = 1911-09-04\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19110904.2.147.1\n| accessdate = 2019-12-15}}</ref>\n| away = Taranaki\n| try1 = [[Albert Asher]] 2, [[Jim Rukutai]], [[Harry Fricker]] 2, [[Bob Mitchell (rugby league)|Bob Mitchell]]\n| con1 = [[Charles Dunning]] 4\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = P Kyle, C Moir, Dan Twohill\n| con2 = [[Arthur Hardgrave]] 3\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 6000\n| referee = Matt Hooper\n}}\n\n===Auckland v Hawke\u2019s Bay M\u0101ori===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 9 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 22\u201310\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Hawke\u2019s Bay Natives v Auckland\n| page = 8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLII| issue=216\n| date = 1911-09-11\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19110911.2.74\n| accessdate = 2019-12-15}}</ref>\n| away = Hawke\u2019s Bay M\u0101ori\n| try1 = Joe Bennett 2, G Hunt, [[Jim Griffen]], [[Albert Asher]], C Linkhorn\n| con1 = [[Charles Dunning]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = W Paewai, Hopi Kani\n| con2 = W Hiha\n| pen2 = W Hiha\n| stadium = Takapuna Racecourse\n| attendance = 500\n| referee = Cunningham\n}}\n\n===Auckland Representative Matches Played and Scorers===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Rank!!Name!!Club!!Play!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Mark!!Points\n|-\n|1||Joe Bennett||Newton Rangers||7||9||-||-||-||27\n|-\n|2||[[Charles Dunning]]||Ponsonby United||6||-||12||1||-||26\n|-\n|3||[[Jim Griffen]]||North Shore Albions||8||4||1||-||-||14\n|-\n|3||[[Albert Asher]]||City Rovers||6||4||1||-||-||14\n|-\n|5||[[Harry Fricker]]||Ponsonby United||6||4||-||-||-||12\n|-\n|5||[[Jim Rukutai]]||Manukau Rovers||6||4||-||-||-||12\n|-\n|7||[[Arthur Carlaw]]||Ponsonby United||6||3||-||-||-||9\n|-\n|7||J Kay||Komakorau (Ngaruawahia Comp.)||3||3||-||-||-||9\n|-\n|9||[[Frank Morse (rugby league)|Frank Morse]]||City Rovers||4||1||1||1||-||7\n|-\n|9||[[George Seagar]]||North Shore Albions||3||1||2||-||-||7\n|-\n|11||[[Alfred Jackson (rugby league)|Alfred Jackson]]||North Shore Albions||8||2||-||-||-||6\n|-\n|11||[[Bob Mitchell (rugby league)|Bob Mitchell]]||City Rovers||5||2||-||-||-||6\n|-\n|11||George Harrison||North Shore Albions||2||2||-||-||-||6\n|-\n|11||[[Stan Walters (rugby league)|Stan Walters]]||North Shore Albions||2||2||-||-||-||6\n|-\n|15||[[Alf Chorley]]||Ponsonby United||3||1||-||-||-||3\n|-\n|15||E Robinson||City Rovers||6||1||-||-||-||3\n|-\n|15||C Linkhorn||Newton Rangers||2||1||-||-||-||3\n|-\n|15||[[Reg Sprague]]||Lower Waikato||1||1||-||-||-||3\n|-\n|15||George Hunt||City Rovers||1||1||-||-||-||3\n|-\n|20||S Cole||Ponsonby United||1||-||1||-||-||2\n|-\n|21||Harry Childs||City Rovers||6||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||C Dillamore||Ponsonby United||2||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||[[Don Kenealy]]||Eden Ramblers||2||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||[[Stan Weston]]||North Shore Albions||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||S Houghton||Ponsonby United||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||J Cummings||Eden Ramblers||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||J O\u2019Sullivan||City Rovers||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||[[Ernie Asher]]||City Rovers||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||[[Ronald MacDonald (rugby league)|Ronald MacDonald]]||North Shore Albions||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|21||Roy Denize||City Rovers||1||-||-||-||-||-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.aucklandleague.co.nz/ Auckland Rugby League Official Site]\n\n[[Category:Auckland Rugby League seasons]]\n[[Category:1911 in New Zealand rugby league|Auckland Rugby League]]\n", "text_old": "The 1911 [[Auckland Rugby League]] season was the second full organised club season in Auckland following the [[1910 Auckland Rugby League season]].\n\n{{s-start}}\n        {{s-bef|before=[[1910 Auckland Rugby League season|1910]]}}\n        {{s-ttl|title=3rd [[Auckland Rugby League]] season\n        |years=\t1911}}\n        {{s-aft|after=[[1912 Auckland Rugby League season|1912]]}}\n        {{end}}\n{{TOC right}}\n\nThe club season commenced on 20 May, with the start of the competition for the Myers Cup. [[City Rovers]] were crowned champions after defeating [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]] in the final 36-15 which was required due to both teams being within 2 points of each other as the competition entered its closing stages. The competition at the time and for decades to come often did not complete full round robins. When a team had an unassailable lead over their nearest rivals the competition was often concluded at that point. Ponsonby and City had already met twice during the season but rather than conclude the round robin with round 10. In round 10 Ponsonby would have had a bye and City would likely have gained an easy win over wooden spooners, Eden Ramblers so the Auckland Rugby League decided to have the two top teams play off for the title a week early rather than prolong the competition.\n\nThe City side featured [[Albert Asher]], [[Alex Stanaway]], [[Jim Rukutai]], and [[Bob Mitchell (rugby league)|Bob Mitchell]], while Ponsonby had [[Charlie Savory]], [[Charles Dunning (rugby)|Charles Dunning]] and [[Arthur Carlaw]].\n\n===Venues===\nUnlike in 1910 when only two venues were used, there were 5 venues used. They were [[Victoria Park, Auckland|Victoria Park]], Takapuna Racecourse, 'Avondale', [[Auckland Domain]], and [[Eden Park]] (which was the venue for the club final between [[City Rovers]] and [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]].\n\n===Eden Ramblers Formed===\nThe senior competition saw the addition of the Eden Ramblers who had been formed in April. A meeting was held at the Avondale Public Hall on Wednesday 26 April with Mr [[John Bollard (politician)|John Bollard, MP]] presiding over it. He was elected president and chairman, and the name Eden Ramblers was chosen along with the colours or green and gold. The following officers were selected: Hon Secretary, Mr B Boone; Management Committee, W. A. Cummings, J Eddoes, W Fairweather, M Morrow, and J Denyer. The membership was close to 50 and they were to begin their training for the season ahead on 29 April with a join practice with Ponsonby at Victoria Park.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Eden Ramblers Club\n| page = 4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=XLVIII| issue=14666\n| date = 1911-04-28\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19110428.2.10\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref>\n\n===Representative Season===\nIt featured a representative program in August and September where [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] played eight matches including two against the New Zealand side. They won seven and lost one. Their first match saw them lose to [[New Zealand national rugby league team|New Zealand]] however they rattled off consecutive wins against New Zealand (6 weeks later), [[Wellington rugby league team|Wellington]], Lower Waikato, [[Hawke's Bay rugby league team|Hawke's Bay]], Nelson, [[Taranaki rugby league team|Taranaki]], and Hawke's Bay M\u0101ori.\n\n==Myers Cup (First Grade Championship)==\nEighteen regular season matches were played before the final on 16 September where [[City Rovers]] defeated [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]] 36 to 15 to retain the title which they had won in 1910.\n\n===Final Standings===\n{|\n|-\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"For\" |F\n!width=20 abbr=\"Against\" |A\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[City Rovers]]\n|8||7||0||1||164||70||'''14'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]]\n|9||7||0||2||205||117||'''14'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[North Shore Albions]]\n|7||3||0||4||80||68||'''6'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Newton Rangers]]\n|7||1||0||6||51||138||'''2'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Eden Ramblers]]\n|7||1||0||6||42||149||'''2'''\n|-\n|}\nThe second round did not feature the final round of matches hence [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]] playing an extra match (when they were due to have a bye), while the table also includes the final played between [[City Rovers|City]] and [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]].\n\n===Results===\n======Round 1======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 May\n| time =\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 19\u20133\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Ponsonby v Newton\n| page = 8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLII| issue=120\n| date = 1911-05-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19110522.2.65\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = [[Charlie Savory]], S Cole, C Dillamore, Syd Riley 2\n| con1 = S Cole 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Sainsbury\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria park\n| attendance =\n| referee = Jaggs\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 May\n| time =\n| home = City\n| score = 13\u20133\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =City v North Shore\n| page = 8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLII| issue=120\n| date = 1911-05-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19110522.2.65\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref>\n| away = North Shore\n| try1 = William Moeki, [[Jim Rukutai]]\n| con1 = [[Alex Stanaway]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Haddon\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance =\n| referee = W Pitts\n}}\n\n======Round 