n\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Australia (Kent Music Report)<ref name=\"kmr\"/>\n|31\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Austria (\u00d63 Austria Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.austriancharts.at:80/1981_single.asp|title=JAHRESHITPARADE 1981|language=German|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903055518/http://www.austriancharts.at:80/1981_single.asp|archivedate=3 September 2011|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|13\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Belgium (Ultratop 50)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=1981|title=Jaaroverzichten 1981|publisher=[[Ultratop]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|19\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canada Top Singles (''RPM'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.4689&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.4689.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.4689|title=Top 100 Singles of 1981|work=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]|publisher=[[Library and Archives Canada]]|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|20\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Germany (Official German Charts)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-1981|title=Top 100 Single-Jahrescharts 1981|publisher=[[GfK Entertainment]]|language=German|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|17\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands (Single Top 100)<ref>{{cite web|title=Jaaroverzichten \u2013 Single 1981|publisher=[[Single Top 100]]|accessdate=March 13, 2018|url=http://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=1981&cat=s|language=nl}}</ref>\n|42\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|South Africa (Springbok Radio)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rock.co.za/files/sahits_1981.html|title=Top 20 Hit Singles of 1981|website=South African Rock Lists|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|1\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Switzerland (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://swisscharts.com/charts/jahreshitparade/1981|title=SWISS YEAR-END CHARTS 1981|language=German|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|6\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|UK Singles (Official Charts Company)<ref>{{cite magazine|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|title=Chart File Top 100|url=http://scans.chartarchive.org/UK/1981/UK%20Charts%201981%20-%20Singles%20and%20albums.pdf|magazine=[[Record Mirror]]|location=London|publisher=Spotlight Publications|page=27|date=December 26, 1981|access-date=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n|8\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Parody==\n\"Bite Your Bum,\" a parody of \"Shaddap You Face,\" was made in 1981 by Australian artists Peter Plus with Bazz and Pilko (Barry Ion and Tony Pilkington). It reached #32 in New Zealand.<ref>[https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=2942 Flavour of New Zealand, 10 May 1981]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|joe-dolce|shaddap-you-face}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n*[http://www.joedolce.net/ Joe Dolce official website]\n*[https://www.facebook.com/pages/Joe-Dolce/106506396133274/ Joe Dolce official Facebook Page]\n\n[[Category:1980 singles]]\n[[Category:Australian pop songs]]\n[[Category:Novelty songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Australia]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Austria]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Belgium]]\n[[Category:European Hot 100 Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Germany]]\n[[Category:Irish Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in South Africa]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:1980 songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about fictional male characters]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1980 single by Joe Dolce}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2011}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Shaddap You Face\n| cover      = Joe Dolce_-_SYF.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Joe Dolce|Joe Dolce Music Theatre]]\n| album      =\n| B-side     = Ain't in No Hurry\n| released   = 1980 (International)<br/>\nApril 1981 (U.S.)\n| format     = [[Vinyl record|7\"]]\n| recorded   = 1980\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[Comedy music|comedy]]\n| length     =\n| label      = [[Full Moon Records]]<br/>[[Epic Records]] (UK)<ref name=\"500 Number One Hits\"/>\n| writer     = Joe Dolce<ref name=\"500 Number One Hits\">{{cite book\n| first= Jo\n| last= Rice\n| year= 1982\n| title= The Guinness Book of 500 Number One Hits\n| edition= 1st\n| publisher= Guinness Superlatives Ltd \n| location= Enfield, Middlesex\n| page= 212\n| isbn= 0-85112-250-7}}</ref>\n| producer   = Joe Dolce and Ian McKenzie<ref name=\"500 Number One Hits\"/>\n| chronology = [[Joe Dolce]]\n| prev_title = Boat People\n| prev_year  = 1979\n| next_title = If You Want to Be Happy\n| next_year  = 1981\n}}\n\"'''Shaddap You Face'''\" is a song written and performed by [[Joe Dolce]] (released under the name Joe Dolce Music Theatre) about a fictitious rebellious [[Italy|Italian]] boy. Released in late 1980, it set a number of sales and longevity records. The song was financed by [[Mike_Brady_(musician)|Mike Brady]]. <ref>[https://iview.abc.net.au/show/classic-countdown/series/0/video/LE1601V005S00  \"Classic Countdown\", 1979 episode, ABC Television, 2017 *The reference comes right at the end of this one hour episode]</ref><ref> https://www.abc.net.au/classiccountdown \"Classic Countdown\", ABC Television, 2017, 1979 episode. This link may work for international audiences with no geoblocks placed on it</ref>\n\n==Sales and chart positions==\n\"Shaddap You Face\" went to number one for eight weeks on the Australia [[Kent Music Report]] in 1980.<ref name=\"kmr\">{{cite book|last=Kent|first=David|title=Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992|edition=Illustrated|publisher=Australian Chart Book|location=St Ives, N.S.W.|year=1993|isbn=0-646-11917-6}}</ref> It reached number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]] on 21 February 1981 and stayed there for three weeks until 14 March 1981\u2014keeping [[Ultravox (band)|Ultravox's]] single \"[[Vienna (Ultravox song)|Vienna]]\" out of the top spot for all the three weeks it was there.<ref name=\"British Hit Singles & Albums\">{{cite book\n| first= David\n| last= Roberts\n| year= 2006\n| title= [[British Hit Singles & Albums]]\n| edition= 19th\n| publisher= Guinness World Records Limited \n| location= London\n| isbn= 1-904994-10-5\n| pages= 390\u20131}}</ref>  The song became the 8th biggest hit of 1981 in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uk-charts.top-source.info/top-100-1981.shtml |title=Top 100 1981 \u2013 UK Music Charts |website=Uk-charts.top-source.info |date= |accessdate=2016-10-23}}</ref>\n\n\"Shaddap You Face\" was also number one in 11 other countries. There have been over 50 different foreign language cover versions, and hundreds more published informally on YouTube with new versions being recorded and uploaded every year. The original release sold over 6 million copies and was the most successful Australian-produced single in Australian music history for many years, with sales of over 450,000 copies. It was Australia's first triple platinum recording by the old count of 100,000 units equalling platinum status, which has since changed to 75,000 units, then 50,000, and finally 70,000 units.{{citation needed|date=July 2013}}\n\nIn the US, the song peaked at number 53 in the summer of 1981 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], number 43 on the ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]'' Top 100,<ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|url=http://50.6.195.142/archives/80s_files/19810627.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-05-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150404235302/http://50.6.195.142/archives/80s_files/19810627.html |archivedate=4 April 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref> and number 24 on ''[[Record World]]''. However, it was regularly played on the [[Dr. Demento]] show to the point of being number six on the year-end Funny 25 that year. In Quebec, \"Shaddap You Face\" reached number one for twelve weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.0326&type=1&interval=50&PHPSESSID=d4aa1bc4o6s09iksf4q7vfcci2 |title=Item Display \u2013 RPM \u2013 Library and Archives Canada |website=Collectionscanada.gc.ca |date= |accessdate=2016-10-23}}</ref>\n\n==Other versions==\n[[Lou Monte]] released a cover of the song in 1981.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I-5EjG-6r9o Lou Monte, \"Shaddap You Face,\" YouTube]</ref> Other notable cover versions have been done by [[KRS-One]] (hip-hop),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wTtjzzeR-HY KRS One, \"Shaddap You Face,\" YouTube]</ref> [[EMF (band)|EMF]] (British),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BTNJP8BNlm8 EMF, \"Shaddap your face,\" YouTube]</ref> [[Andrew Sachs]] (Manuel, of ''Fawlty Towers''), Werner B\u00f6hm, alias: Gottlieb Wendehals (German, title: Mensch, \u00e4rger dich nicht),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cizOXtMNgio Gottlieb Wendehals, \"Mensch, \u00e4rger dich nicht,\" YouTube]</ref> Sheila (French, titled: Et Ne La Ram\u00e8ne Pas),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tLlPRfjusYc SHEILA, \"Et ne la ramene pas,\" YouTube]</ref> Dingetje (Dutch, titled: Houtochdiekop),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C5fbE0_YnTw Dingetje, \"Houtochdiekop,\" YouTube]</ref> De Strangers (muziekgroep (Dutch, titled: Agget Mor Fret),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wZ1za2gXuR8 De Strangers, \"Agget mor fret,\" YouTube]</ref> Volker Rosin und die Lollypops (German, titled: H\u00f6rst du nicht die Kuh - Muh!), [[Franco Franchi]] with the duo, Franco e Ciccio (Italian, title: Al\u00ec Al\u00ec Al\u00e8),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2LkUcas74gc Franco e Ciccio, \"Al\u00ec Al\u00ec Al\u00e8,\" YouTube]</ref> an Aboriginal language version by Gnarnyarrhe Waitairie, a Papua New Guinean version by The Breeze Band (title: \"Pasim Pes Bilong Yu\" \u2013 pidgin version),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CFeEF65QsM0 Papua New Guinea Breeze Band, \"Pasim Pes Bilong Yu,\" YouTube]</ref> and a spoken word interpretation by [[Samuel L. Jackson]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GsDQ93iguP8 Samuel L. Jackson, \"Shaddap You Face,\" YouTube]</ref>\n\nThe [[National Folk Festival (Australia)|National Folk Festival]] in [[Canberra]] featured 'The Inspired Shaddap You Face Contest' in April 2006.  Festival artists were invited to perform their interpretations of the classic song. The Cygnet Folk Festival in Tasmania featured the second 'Inspired Shaddap You Face Contest' in the following year. [[Joe Dolce]] was invited to be the MC at both events.\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (1980\u20131981)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak <br> position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Australia ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref name=\"kmr\"/>\n|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|1|artist=Joe Dolce Music Theatre|song=Shaddap You Face|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|1|artist=Joe Dolce Music Theatre|song=Shaddap You Face|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadatopsingles|2|chartid=0376|rowheader=true|accessdate=22 August 2019}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|France ([[Institut fran\u00e7ais d'opinion publique|IFOP]]){{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|1|songid=720|artist=Joe Dolce Music Theatre|song=Shaddap You Face|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|1|song=Shaddap Your Face|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch40|4|year=1981|week=14|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|4|artist=Joe Dolce Music Theatre|song=Shaddap You Face|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|1|artist=Joe Dolce Music Theatre|song=Shaddap You Face|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Norway|2|artist=Joe Dolce Music Theatre|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|South Africa ([[Springbok Radio]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rock.co.za/files/sa_number_1s_69_89.html|title=SA Number 1s 1965 - 1989|website=rock.co.za|accessdate=2018-05-26}}</ref>\n|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|5|artist=Joe Dolce Music Theatre|song=Shaddap You Face|rowheader=true|accessdate=22 August 2019}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|1|artist=Joe Dolce Music Theatre|song=Shaddap You Face|rowheader=true|accessdate=22 August 2019}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|1|date=19810221|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|53|artist=Joe Dolce Music Theatre|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 June 2018}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US ''[[Cash Box]]'' Top 100<ref name=\"autogenerated2\"/>\n|43\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US ''[[Record World]]'' {{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n|24\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (1980)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Australia (Kent Music Report)<ref name=\"kmr\"/>\n|45\n|}\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (1981)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Australia (Kent Music Report)<ref name=\"kmr\"/>\n|31\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Austria (\u00d63 Austria Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.austriancharts.at:80/1981_single.asp|title=JAHRESHITPARADE 1981|language=German|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903055518/http://www.austriancharts.at:80/1981_single.asp|archivedate=3 September 2011|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|13\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Belgium (Ultratop 50)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=1981|title=Jaaroverzichten 1981|publisher=[[Ultratop]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|19\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canada Top Singles (''RPM'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.